<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-657-761  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 657 761.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Dec 4 1990 v4 n41 p30(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>In Focus unveils lightweight LCD screens that display 5,000colors. (In Focus Systems Inc.'s liquid crystal displays)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McManus, Neil; Howard, Stephen.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   In Focus Systems Inc. (Product development).andO;Topic:     Liquid Crystal DisplaysProduct DevelopmentColor.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Neil McManus and Stephen HowardandM;Tualatin, Ore.andP;  -- In Focus Systems Inc. last month announced what it billedas the first lightweight color LCD screens.andM;The new Direct View screens  are due in March in two versions, each with aresolution of 640 by 480 pixels: The 5000M will offer almost 5,000 colors,while the 64M model will provide a palette of 64 colors.andM;The units are only 2 to 3 inches thick, weigh about 6 pounds and provide aviewing area measuring 10.5 inches diagonally.andM;The new displays use In Focus' patented passive-matrix technology, in whichlight from an outside source passes through the pixels of stacked panels.andO;They have incandescent back-lighting and do not emit low-frequencyelectromagnetic radiation, according to In Focus.andM;The company said it has not yet decided whether to offer its own Mac videoadapters or work with existing display cards, but it said the screens willwork with the Mac SE (in black and white) and with the Mac II family, as wellas IBM Corp.'s CGA, EGA and VGA standards.andM;Because of the slow refresh times of LCD panels, they are not appropriate foranimation, the company said.andM;Retail prices for the Direct View screens will range from $2,500 to $4,000,depending on whether cards are included.andP;  The displays also will be offeredon an OEM basis.andM;In Focus Systems Inc. is at 7770 S.W.andP;  Mohawk St., Tualatin, Ore.andP;  97062.andO;Phone (503) 692-4968 or (800) 327-7231; fax (503) 692-4476.andO;</TEXT></DOC>